							</div>

							<div class="bio-container">
					<div class="bio-img-container">
						<div class="bio-img">
							<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2143304-150x150.jpeg" width="96" height="96" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2143304-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Jeff Wilser" class="avatar avatar-96 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-96 alignnone photo" />						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Jeff Wilser</h4>
												<p>Jeff Wilser is the author of six books, including Alexander Hamilton’s Guide to Life and The Good News About What’s Bad for You . . . and The Bad News About What’s Good for You. His work has appeared in print or online at GQ, Esquire, Time, New York magazine, Glamour, Cosmo, mental_floss, MTV, and the HuffPost. His advice has been syndicated to a network of two hundred newspapers including the Miami Herald and the Chicago Tribune. He grew up in Texas, used to live in New York, and is now traveling the world indefinitely.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
